  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (MRL 3, W-EP-04)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 3. Seven factors are assessed with achieved levels at or near required levels; three factors are flagged as not-assessed on grounds that they fall 'beyond the scope of the current submission cycle.' At MRL 3, each unassessed factor constitutes a material epistemic gap. Decision is recorded as Accepted despite these gaps, which is the targeted weakness.",
